cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG 

The paper deals with video manipulation detection, which involves analyzing multimedia stream descriptors rather than pixel data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Among these, cs.MM and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to multimedia and image/video analysis. However, cs.CR and cs.IR are also relevant, as they deal with security and data manipulation. Finally, cs.LG is a possibility, as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach to manipulation detection.
